<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="129" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">314.0022/4: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Jorge Ubico</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName> [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-15">undated</date>.]<lb/>[Received December 15, 1930—3:10
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Greatly obliged. Express my highest esteem for United States on the
                            occasion of your very opportune protection.</p>
                        <p>Sincerely your friend,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">General Jorge
                            Ubico</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>